Package org.neo4j.kernel.api.query

Class ExecutingQueryStatus

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.neo4j.kernel.api.query.ExecutingQueryStatus
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    SimpleState, WaitingOnLock
    abstract class ExecutingQueryStatus
extends Object
    Internal representation of the status of an executing query.

    This is used for inspecting the state of a query.

    See Also:

      • waitTimeNanos

        abstract long waitTimeNanos​(long currentTimeNanos)
        Time in nanoseconds that has been spent waiting in the current state. This is the portion of wait time not included in the ExecutingQuery.waitTimeNanos field.
        Parameters:
        currentTimeNanos - the current timestamp on the nano clock.
        Returns:
        the time between the time this state started waiting and the provided timestamp.

      • waitingOnLocks

        List<ActiveLock> waitingOnLocks()
        List of locks query is waiting on. Will be empty for all of the statuses except for WaitingOnLock.
        Returns:
        list of locks query is waiting on, empty list if query is not waiting.
